Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and remove strings from @Sugar Snap Peas{4%ounce}. Quarter @Lime{1}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Once water is boiling, add @Lo Mein Noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

While noodles cook, rinse @Shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add shrimp, snap peas, and @Bok Choy and Napa Cabbage{4%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender and shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and @Korean Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste into pan with shrimp and veggies. Cook, stirring, until coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Stir in drained noodles and juice from two lime wedges (four wedges for 4) until thoroughly coated and combined. Taste and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, transfer everything to a large bowl to combine.

Divide lo mein between shallow bowls. Garnish with @Peanuts{1/2%ounce} and cilantro.

> For an extra-nutty crunch, toast peanuts in a hot dry pan!

Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.